body:
While elaborating the Verilog module below, Yosys rapidly hogs memory (multiple GB) and does not seem to finish. If the counter increment is changed to the examples in the comment, everything works fine. Although it can be easily avoided, I assume `i = i + 1'b1` is still valid syntax and hence should be supported by Yosys.
``` Verilog
module yosys_loop_increment(trigger_i, data_o);

   input trigger_i;
   output [7:0] data_o;

    parameter DEPTH = 5;
   integer i;

   always @(*) begin
      data_o = 8'b0;
      if(trigger_i) begin
         // working: i = i + 1 or i = i + 2'b1 or i = i + 32'b1 or i = i + 'b1
         for(i = 0; i < DEPTH; i = i + 1'b1) begin
            data_o = data_o + i;
         end
      end
   end
          
endmodule
```
